article.headline: Arkansas 70, Memphis 54
article.story:
MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) -- Charity Ford scored 15 points, Dominique
Washington added 12 and Lauren Ervin grabbed 11 rebounds to lead
No. 24 Arkansas to a 70-54 victory over Memphis on Monday night.

Arkansas (12-1) won its fifth straight and improved to 6-0 on
the road. The Razorbacks' only loss this season came last month to
second-ranked North Carolina in Hawaii.

Devin Necaise scored 14 to lead Memphis (3-9). Reserve Hope
Adams had 12 points and 10 rebounds.

Ranked in the Top 25 for the first time in four years, the
Razorbacks struggled in the first half against Memphis. Arkansas
shot 34.4 percent and led 34-26 at the break.

Memphis missed 10 of its first 11 shots and committed turnovers
on five of its first six possessions, but scrambled to tie the game
14-all with 8 minutes left in the first half.

After the break, Arkansas shot 46.2 percent and broke away from
the Tigers by going on an early 12-3 run for a 51-34 advantage.

Memphis shot 29 percent in the second half and 25 percent for
the game. The Tigers were 17-of-68 from the field and 4-of-22 from
3-point range.

Arkansas point guard Brittney Vaughn, who entered the game
averaging 12 assists during the past six games, was held to two
assists and played only 10 minutes.
